FR941027-2-00037 FR941027-2-00025 [FRL&hyph;5097&hyph;7] Norcross Mercury Spill Site; Notice of Proposed Settlement AGENCY: Environmental Protection Agency. ACTION: Notice of proposed settlement. SUMMARY: Under Section 122(h) of the Comprehensive Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) has offered to potentially responsible party a Cost Recovery Agreement to settle claims for past and future removal actions at the Norcross Mercury Spill Site, Norcross, Georgia. EPA will consider public comments on the proposed settlement for thirty (30) days. EPA may withdraw from or modify the proposed settlement should such comments disclose facts or considerations which indicate the proposed settlement is inappropriate, improper, or inadequate. Copies of the proposed settlement are available from: Ms. Carolyn McCall, Waste Management Division, U.S. EPA, Region IV, 345 Courtland Street NE., Atlanta, Georgia 30365, 404/347&hyph;5059. Written comments may be submitted to Ms. McCall within 30 days of the date of publication. Dated: October 14, 1994. Richard D. Green, Deputy Director. [FR Doc. 94&hyph;26664 Filed 10&hyph;26&hyph;94; 8:45 am] BILLING CODE 6560&hyph;50&hyph;M
